Hi Terrell,

I second Joe's thoughts... your document is awesome!  Very thorough and 
thoughtful.

I have a few notes regarding details of a few areas with which I have 
some familiarity:

1.  The "known" wav files that provide a starting point for testing 
_*are*_ in the repository.  Previously I had mistakenly said that they 
are not, but Joe corrected me several days ago.  They are in the 
~.samples directory.

2.  I have modernized the MAP65 code but my changes are not yet in the 
github codebase.  An earlier version of my code is in branch 
develop-fort but the code there is not at all up to date and I really 
should just delete that branch.

When I build the "stock" v3.0.0_test branch with gcc 15.2.0 here, 
testing with strict flags, over the entire  wsjtx codebase I get 5874 
build errors. 500 of those errors are in MAP65.

When I build my modernized MAP65 code with gcc 15.2.0 here with strict 
flags, instead of the 500 errors gotten with the MAP65 code in 
v3.0.0_test I get zero build errors. So this newer MAP65 code does well 
with the gcc 15.2.0 compiler here.  I will eventually upload this code 
to our github repository.  If you want to review the code before then 
let me know and I will post a tarball.

3. Qt6.  We have had a branch that compiles and runs fine with Qt6 for 
at least a couple of years.  It "works" through at least Qt 6.10.1;  I 
have not tested it beyond that Qt version.  This code is on BB and I was 
keeping it up to date until sometime in mid February but I have not been 
doing so since then.  So some work would need to be done to port this to 
our github code given the divergence in the two codebases since then.  
But that might still be easier than starting from scratch.  If you want 
to see this code let me know and I will post a tarball.

Thanks again for this absolutely superb, comprehensive document Terrell!

73,

Roger

