      strict flags, instead of the 500 errors gotten with the MAP65 code
      in v3.0.0_test I get zero build errors. So this newer MAP65 code
      does well with the gcc 15.2.0 compiler here.  I will eventually
      upload this code to our github repository.  If you want to review
      the code before then let me know and I will post a tarball.  <br>
      <br>
      3. Qt6.  We have had a branch that compiles and runs fine with Qt6
      for at least a couple of years.  It "works" through at least Qt
      6.10.1;  I have not tested it beyond that Qt version.  This code
      is on BB and I was keeping it up to date until sometime in mid
      February but I have not been doing so since then.  So some work
      would need to be done to port this to our github code given the
      divergence in the two codebases since then.  But that might still
      be easier than starting from scratch.  If you want to see this
      code let me know and I will post a tarball.  <br>
      <br>
      Thanks again for this absolutely superb, comprehensive document
      Terrell!<br>
      <br>
      73,<br>
      <br>
      Roger<br>
